A: The error you're seeing is not related to AES or TripleDES, but rather to the way you're handling the data.
When you're using PKCS5Padding, the data must be padded to a multiple of the block size. In the case of AES, the block size is 16 bytes. So, if your plaintext is not a multiple of 16 bytes, you'll get an IllegalBlockSizeException.
You can use PKCS5Padding with AES, but you need to ensure that your plaintext is a multiple of 16 bytes. If it's not, you can pad it with spaces or other characters until it is.
